{
  "text": "An independent study on sixty-one painful hip and knee arthroplasties or before second stage reimplantation showed a sensitivity and specificity of α-defensine testing of 100% and 95%, respectively. This test demonstrated better sensitivity and specificity when compared to culture, SF leukocyte count, ESR and CRP. No data about systemic inflammatory comorbidities or metallosis was presented [CITATION_1] .",
